record.title: ADVANCING AMERICA'S PRIORITIES ACT--MOTION TO PROCEED
record.narrative:
ADVANCING AMERICA'S PRIORITIES ACT--MOTION TO PROCEED -- (Senate - September 17, 2008)

[Page: S8934]

speaking.paragraph: Mr. President, I move to proceed to Calendar No. 894, S. 3297, and I send a cloture motion to the desk.

record.chair: The cloture motion having been presented under rule XXII, the Chair directs the clerk to read the motion.
record.narrative: The legislative clerk read as follows:

We, the undersigned Senators, in accordance with the provisions of rule XXII of the Standing Rules of the Senate, hereby move to bring to a close debate on the motion to proceed to Calendar No. 894, S. 3297, the Advancing America's Priorities Act.

speaking.paragraph: Mr. President, I now withdraw that motion.
